I've done this several times (8+) with restarting the browser and I keep running into the same problem. 

(1) At first i thought it might be related to having the space in the config_path because it's on a Google Shared drive, so it formats oddly in the config file, but if I trained using that path, and it's still creating the files it's suppose to in the right destinations.

(2) All the files in the training-dataset are there .csv (202 KB), .h5 (119KB), .pickle 148 (KB), .mat (175 KB). And from what I see from the CSV file, all the labeled data is there.

(3) I could delete all other snapshots in the dlc-models>>test folder, but I don't think that is the case. And the snapshot-23000.data-00000-of-00001 (96MB), snapshot-230000.index (11KB), snapshot-230000(2MB) -- which I believe suggests that all the training was stored correctly.

(3a) The empty files that are produced **the second time in the evaluation** results are: 
a) DeepCut_resnet50_FheadOrientation-moving_arudinoJun27shuffle1_230000-results.csv (153 bytes)
b) DeepCut_resnet50_headOrientation-moving_arudinoJun27shuffle1_230000-results.h5 (1KB), 
3) DeepCut_resnet50_headOrientation-moving_arudinoJun27shuffle1_230000-snapshot-230000.h5 (215KB)

And it's here (as well as when it reports that it has been evaluated but no reports are given) that I can see that the .csv file is empty. 

(4) One thing I don't think would affect it is that my videos folder right now doesn't have links to the videos (since I migrated everything to Google Collab after initializing and labeling on GUI. So the shortcuts to the video files didn't migrate correctly (maybe because it was also on Google Drive > Shared? But I don't think that's relevant to evaluation process.
